# EWP-003 — Tenant

**Engine:** VS08 – License, Subscription & Tenant Management Engine

**Milestone:** VS08A – Tenant Foundation

**Capability Contract:** CC-003 – Tenant

**Status:** Approved for Implementation

---

# Objective

Implement the **Tenant** aggregate exactly as defined by the approved CAP architecture.

The Tenant aggregate establishes the primary commercial and security boundary of the platform.

---

# Inputs

Implementation shall comply with:

* ES-001 Database Standards

* ES-008 Architecture & Domain Modeling

* ES-009 Data Ownership & Persistence

* ES-010 Platform Naming & Namespace

* ADR-008-001 through ADR-008-013

* DDS-101A

* CC-003

---

# Scope

Implement only the Tenant aggregate.

---

## Domain

Implement:

* Aggregate Root
* Lifecycle management
* Domain validation

---

## Persistence

Implement:

* Prisma model
* Database migration
* Repository interface
* Repository implementation

---

## Application Layer

Implement:

* Register Tenant
* Activate Tenant
* Suspend Tenant
* Archive Tenant
* Get Tenant by Id
* Get Tenant by Code
* List Tenants

---

## Validation

Validate:

* Unique TenantCode
* Unique TenantName
* Valid lifecycle transitions
* Immutable TenantCode

---

## Testing

Implement:

* Unit tests
* Repository tests
* PostgreSQL integration tests

---

# Explicit Exclusions

Do **NOT** implement:

* TenantWorkspace
* WorkspaceInstallation
* Subscription
* Licensing
* Billing
* Membership
* Feature Flags
* Runtime

---

# Repository Requirements

Implement:

* Create
* Activate
* Suspend
* Archive
* GetById
* GetByCode
* List
* ExistsCode
* ExistsName

---

# Acceptance Criteria

The work package is complete only when:

* Aggregate implemented.
* Migration succeeds.
* Repository tests pass.
* Integration tests pass.
* Lifecycle validation implemented.
* Audit fields implemented.
* Soft delete implemented.
* No architecture violations.
* No TODO comments.
* No placeholder implementations.

